  "connection_to_palindrome": {
    "explanation": "The C\u03a8=1/4 crossing is a consequence of palindromic spectral symmetry in the single-qubit Liouvillian. The 4x4 Liouvillian has eigenvalues that pair as \u03bb + \u03bb' = -2*sum_gamma. The crossing time t* is where these paired modes produce C\u03a8=1/4. Using T2* (not T2 echo) validates that the FREE INDUCTION decay rate governs the crossing, not the refocused rate.",
    "key_test": "If crossing matches T2*-based prediction (not T2echo-based), it confirms: (1) palindrome theory is correct, (2) T2* is the relevant timescale, (3) echo refocusing does not affect the crossing equation."
  }
}